<br>
Vital Statistics: <br>
    Date: Friday, August 18th, 2000 <br>
    Time: 8p.m. Eastern, 5 pacific <br>
    Place: The Arena, off of Lake Rathetear <br>
<br>
The tournament's competitors will form their own teams within various weight classes: <br>
    Feather Weights - Level 11-15 <br>
    Light Weights - Level 16-20 <br>
    Medium Weights - Level 21-25 <br>
    Heavy Weights - Level 26-30 <br>
    Super Heavy Weights - Level 31-35 <br>
<br>
    The level restrictions will be strictly enforced downwards, but competitors wishing to enter into a higher weight class than befits their level are free to do so. For example, a level 25 player is free to enter into the Heavy Weights, but a level 26 player may not enter the Medium weights. <br>
<br>
    Each team will have three players of any race or class, no more, and no less. <br>
<br>
    Prizes: <br>
    The combatants of each winning team will be individually rewarded very well, with item or monetary prizes. Alcohol will be provided to all who desire it! <br>
<br>
Basic Tournament Rules will be followed: <br>
    No buffs will be allowed prior to combat. Cancel magic spells will enforce this policy. Noticeably heavy twinks will also not be allowed to participate. Magical pets will be allowed for all pet summoning classes.  Interference by a third party in any combat will result in that person's expulsion from the tournament, a restart of the combat, and will likely incur the wrath of the gods. All combatants will be required to stay on the main platform in the Arena during their combats, while all spectators will be asked to remain at the periphery of the platform. <br>
<br>
To Sign Up: <br>
    Have your team at the Arena by the specified time, and follow our directions for which Soul Cadre official you should contact to enter into your chosen weight class. Each team should appoint a group leader, who will sign you up, and pay the entrance fee of 5 gold pieces per level of each entrant in the group ( IE 3 level 30's pay 45pp to enter the group). In the interest of cooperation, and expediting play, please follow instructions given by the Tournament Officials on the scene. <br>
<br>
    We look forward to hosting this event for the Torvonnilous community, and hope that all you brave Souls out there will join us for the festivities! <br>
<br>
    <br>
Bazzer Fox <br>
1st Lieutenant <br>
